The optimal ratio between the photons collector “ZnFe2O4” and the electrons acceptor “TiO2” is investigated (Fig. 9) and the best performance occurs for ZnFe2O4/TiO2: 75 %/25 with a potential VD of 0.67 V. ZnFe2O4 governs the efficiency and catalyzes the downhill reaction (∆G° = −557 kcal mol−1):Fig. 9
